Powell et al. (2013) suggests specific molecular strategies (e.g., β-blockade) and cellular biomarkers (e.g., CD16
− monocytes) that could potentially be harnessed in future studies to develop health-protective interventions. Other alternatives could be considered with potential for application in clinical and health settings, such as meditation, yoga, praying, or tai-chi (
Holmes et al., 2019; 
Boyle et al., 2019; 
Mañas et al., 2010).
